<span id="freeTextContainer10766083318918534106">The Milagro Beanfield War as a recipe:<br/><br/>In a large bowl, add equal parts John Irving, Ken Kesey, Berkeley CA, and New Mexico. Mix well and bake under a desert sun until parched. <br/><br/>Serve caliente with a side of frijoles, warm tortillas, and liberal amounts of hot sauce. <br/><br/>The result is a mildly satisfying yet complex dish with flavors of history, race and ethnicity, and land and water rights.<br/><br/>Buen Provecho!</span>

